From: Hiral Patel <hiral.patel@qlogic.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Oct 2014 10:44:49 -0700
Subject: bnx2fc: Fix 'bnx2fc: Fix FCP RSP residual parsing.'
Patch-Mainline: Not yet
References: bnc#909367,FATE#317542

Use bitwise or instead of logical or.

Signed-off-by: Hiral Patel <hiral.patel@qlogic.com>
Acked-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/scsi/bnx2fc/bnx2fc_io.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/scsi/bnx2fc/bnx2fc_io.c b/drivers/scsi/bnx2fc/bnx2fc_io.c
index a69a85b9..4e4fe81 100644
--- a/drivers/scsi/bnx2fc/bnx2fc_io.c
+++ b/drivers/scsi/bnx2fc/bnx2fc_io.c
@@ -1775,7 +1775,7 @@ static void bnx2fc_parse_fcp_rsp(struct bnx2fc_cmd *io_req,
 
 	io_req->fcp_status = FC_GOOD;
 	io_req->fcp_resid = 0;
-	if (rsp_flags & (FCOE_FCP_RSP_FLAGS_FCP_RESID_OVER ||
+	if (rsp_flags & (FCOE_FCP_RSP_FLAGS_FCP_RESID_OVER |
 	    FCOE_FCP_RSP_FLAGS_FCP_RESID_UNDER))
 		io_req->fcp_resid = fcp_rsp->fcp_resid;
 
